        <abstract> 
<p>Summarises the "remarkable facts about the movements of plants" in Fritz Müller’s letter of January [<hi rend="doubleUnderline">12996</hi>]. CD comments that Müller’s observations support the conclusion that he and Francis Darwin arrived at – that leaves go to sleep to escape the full effects of radiation.</p> 
        </abstract>
